> Meant-to-be duos: peanut butter & jelly, sun & sand, Homer & Marge, shrimp & grits. Just like the others listed, it's clear that opposites attract. In this case, smooth and creamy grits perfectly complement the slightly-smoky, succulent seared shrimp. There's also lightly charred bell pepper and a buttery sauce. Never made it yourself? Now's your chance! Luckily, this version couldn't be quicker or easier—all you need is 25 minutes for this dynamic dish to hit your dinner table.

Wash and dry all produce.

Halve, core, and thinly slice @bell pepper{1}(halved, cored, and thinly sliced) into strips. Trim and thinly slice @scallions{2}(trimmed and thinly sliced), separating whites from greens.

== Grits ==

In a #small pot{}, combine @water{2%cups}, half the @veggie stock concentrate{1}(using half now, save rest for later), and @salt{1%tsp}. Bring to a boil over high heat.

Once water is boiling, slowly whisk in @polenta{1/2%cup} (this prevents clumping), then cover and reduce heat to medium low. Simmer for ~{5%minutes}.

Turn off heat; whisk in @cream cheese{4%tbsp}, @Monterey Jack cheese{1/4%cup}, and @butter{2%tbsp} until melted and smooth. Keep covered off heat until ready to serve.

> For 4 servings: Use a medium pot with 4 cups water and 2 tsp salt. Use 4 TBSP butter.

== Bell Pepper ==

While grits simmer, heat a drizzle of @olive oil{1%tsp}(for bell pepper) in a #large pan{} over medium-high heat. Add bell pepper, @salt{pinch}, and @pepper{pinch}. Cook, stirring occasionally, until softened, ~{6-8%minutes}.

Turn off heat; transfer to a #plate{}. Wipe out pan.

== Shrimp ==

Rinse @shrimp{10%oz} under cold water, then pat dry with #paper towels{}. Season all over with @smoked paprika{1%tsp}, @garlic powder{1%tsp}, and a big pinch of salt and pepper.

Heat a large drizzle of @olive oil{4%tsp}(for shrimp) in pan used for bell pepper over medium-high heat. Add shrimp and scallion whites; cook, stirring occasionally, until shrimp is almost cooked through, ~{2-3%minutes} (it'll finish cooking in next step).

Stir bell pepper, @water{1/4%cup}, and remaining @veggie stock concentrate{1}(using remaining concentrate) into pan with shrimp. Bring to a simmer. Cook, stirring, until shrimp is cooked through and sauce is slightly thickened, ~{1-2%minutes}.

Turn off heat; stir in @butter{1%tbsp} until melted.

== To Serve ==

Uncover pot with grits; stir in water a few tablespoons at a time until mixture reaches the consistency of porridge. Season with salt and pepper.

Divide grits between shallow #bowls{}. Top with shrimp mixture and any remaining sauce. Garnish with scallion greens. Drizzle with @hot sauce{1%tsp} if desired and serve.